  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed roof extensions to the main dwellinghouse and above the rear outrigger, by reason of their inappropriate detailed design, scale, siting, form and massing, would form a dominant and discordant addition to the host property and wider terrace setting and would be readily visible from the surrounding private realm. The extensions would dominate the host property and detract from the historic character of the property. The proposed development is therefore contrary to the NPPF (2021), Policies D1 and D4 of the London Plan (2021), Policy CS8 of the Islington Core Strategy (2011), Policy DM2.1 of the Development Management Policies (2013) and Islington's Urban Design Guide (2017)."
